            <p>259 West 45<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street.<lb/>
                Sunday Nov 2&#47;84<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>The last rites were given to our<lb/>&#91;&#94;&#93; departed  friend Levison last evening by &#34;Hebab&#34;¬ù&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> in preparing his body rendering it in a<lb/> casket to sent<sic></sic> to St Louis for interment<lb/> this pm. he died quietly at 1 oC yester<lb/>&#45;day morning&#8212;he had been unconscious<lb/> for three or four days &#38; was 12 days<lb/> without nourishment of any kind except<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the wetting of his lips with a few drops<lb/> of water&#8212;poor fellow it was a sad<lb/>ending&#45;&#45; I am happy to say that<lb/> my dear Mother is to day pronounced<lb/> by the physician as better &#38; please God<lb/> in a few days hope will be able to say<lb/> that all danger is past&#8212;With<lb/> kind regards from Mrs Allen as well<lb/> as myself  &#38; thanking you for your<lb/> kind wishes  for My Mother I am<lb/></p>		
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                H.S. Allen<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                The opening of our Montefiore Home was a great success<lb/></p>
        </body>
